{"id": "EUVD-2022-55175", "enisaUuid": "f82d5601-a3b4-35b5-b2e7-fed6d5c58c9f", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nperf/x86/amd: fix potential integer overflow on shift of a int\n\nThe left shift of int 32 bit integer constant 1 is evaluated using 32 bit\narithmetic and then passed as a 64 bit function argument. In the case where\ni is 32 or more this can lead to an overflow.  Avoid this by shifting\nusing the BIT_ULL macro instead.", "datePublished": "2025-03-27T16:42:57", "dateUpdated": "2025-10-01T17:23:40", "baseScore": 5.5, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H", "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/fbf7b0e4cef3b5470b610f14fb9faa5ee7f63954", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/f84c9b72fb200633774704d8020f769c88a4b249", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/14cc13e433e1067557435b1adbf05608d7d47a93", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/a4d01fb87ece45d4164fd725890211ccf9a307a9", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/08245672cdc6505550d1a5020603b0a8d4a6dcc7"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-49748"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "27b87378-71cb-3733-b50d-0d7eae756a66", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.4.231"}, {"id": "450e85af-95a3-3acc-977e-eb79745c2216", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.2"}, {"id": "456a944a-d20a-3237-9d9c-372b4342ce37", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "3512462036dbe44d88e93e75ee8a993781183ddb"}, {"id": "4d9f5e32-1e87-337c-845b-e053d9b9b47d", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "5cc041e6-f3c8-3ac8-aac8-6a9c52e2d1f0", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.1.9"}, {"id": "6e25e760-bd6a-34bf-a0eb-693d97789ac7", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5.6"}, {"id": "70fe1b88-7185-323a-8a9b-50ef201844d6", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "471af006a747f1c535c8a8c6c0973c320fe01b22 <0824567